%H A367185 MathOverflow, <a href="https://mathoverflow.net/questions/458129/maximizing-a-sum-minus-its-maximal-summand">Maximizing a sum minus its maximal summand</a>
%e A367185 For n = 4, the best permutation is [1, 4, 3, 2], with a(4) = (1*1+2*4+3*3+4*2) - max(1*1,2*4,3*3,4*2) = 26 - 9 = 17.
